FBIS3-60872 "jptot001__l94120" JPRS-TOT-94-001-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Terrorism FOUO 7 January 1994 CENTRAL EURASIA RUSSIA Four Caucasians Kidnap Children; No Motive Given Hijackers Have Criminal Records PM2912111193 Moscow ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI in Russian 29 Dec 93 First Edition p 1 PM2912111193 Moscow ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Nikolay Modestov report: "A Unique Incident -- So Declared Russian First Vice Premier Oleg Soskovets at a Press Conference Held After the Release of the Hostages"] [Excerpts] The situation's uniqueness consisted not only in the technical parameters of the helicopter, which were unusual for this type of crime -- the single entrance door to the craft, the maneuverability in flight, the cramped and enclosed nature of the cabin -- but also in the large number of schoolchildren seized by the terrorists, and the professionalism of one of the bandits (who was a former military pilot), as well as the degree to which the criminals were armed, and their aggressiveness. [passage omitted] Suffice it to say that the gang's ringleader has three criminal convictions, and one of its members was tried for rape. Oleg Soskovets also noted the courage and endurance of the pilots. The main responsibility for dealing with the gang lay with those subordinate to First Deputy Internal Affairs Minister Mikhail Yegorov. However, all the heads of oblasts and the rayons in the North Caucasus, even of those regions where a state of emergency is currently in force, took part in resolving the situation. [passage omitted]
